text.tspan: An ancient city of stone and paper, Landly is made
of and for churches. How the stone floats is a
mistery, but it's worn down and cracked by time,
the chunks floating off one after another, sometimes
large enough to become small villages of their own.
Its scape is defined mostly by the churches that
compose it: Every building, large or small, is a
wildly diferent church, used as schooles and homes
